Description: Implements density, distribution, quantile, and random generation
    functions for Burr Type III, Burr Type X, Burr Type XII, and a derived
    Burr-like distribution. These distributions provide flexible parametric
    models for positive-valued event times and can represent a wide range of
    tail behaviours and hazard shapes. They are particularly useful for
    modelling incubation periods and other epidemiological delay
    distributions where skewness and heavy tails are common. The package
    provides a consistent interface for working with these distributions in
    statistical workflows involving simulation, likelihood-based inference,
    and delay distribution modelling.
